Place roast on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. In a skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil until tender. Add the marmalade, pecans and cinnamon; cook and stir until marmalade is melted. Spoon over roast. Bake, uncovered, at 325 degrees F for 1-3/4 hours or until meat thermometer reads 145 degrees F (63 degrees C). Let stand for 10 minutes before slicing.